<subSubSection id="13DE65452438FF46FF349DB9FEFC30B8" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5B7B36CE2438FF46FF349DB9FEFC30B8" blockId="1.[151,1437,153,990]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">
<emphasis id="69B0EADC2438FF46FF349DB9FE823183" bold="true" box="[199,315,716,742]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="9CC44D4D2438FF46FEB19DB9FE483183" authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="2019" box="[322,497,716,742]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Suwallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jihuae">
<emphasis id="69B0EADC2438FF46FEB19DB9FE483183" box="[322,497,716,742]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">Suwallia jihuae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="9CC44D4D2438FF46FD339DB8FCC83183" authorityName="Du &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2015" box="[704,881,716,743]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Suwallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wolongshana">
<emphasis id="69B0EADC2438FF46FD339DB8FCC83183" box="[704,881,716,743]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">S. wolongshana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sharing comparable body color but can be distinguished in the male by the strongly sclerotized hemitergal processes, the dark pigmented tibia, and by the H-shaped median sclerite on tergum 10, a character unknown in other 
<taxonomicName id="9CC44D4D2438FF46FCA69C67FC0E3049" authorityName="Ricker" authorityYear="1943" box="[853,951,786,812]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Suwallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="69B0EADC2438FF46FCA69C67FC0E3049" box="[853,951,786,812]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">Suwallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species. The male of 
<taxonomicName id="9CC44D4D2438FF46FB4A9C66FAD43049" authorityName="Du &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2015" box="[1209,1389,786,813]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Suwallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wolongshana">
<emphasis id="69B0EADC2438FF46FB4A9C66FAD43049" box="[1209,1389,786,813]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">S. wolongshana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has unsclerotized hemitergal processes, two longitudinal sclerotized bands on median portion of tergum 10 (see figs. 2, 3, 
<quantity id="9C3C9B2B2438FF46FF3C9C2CFF433016" box="[207,250,857,883]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.778" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" unit="in" value="7.0">7 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="3F554B3F2438FF46FEF29C2CFE7D3016" author="Chen, Z. T. &amp; Du, Y. Z." box="[257,452,856,883]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" pagination="297 - 300" refId="ref2165" refString="Chen, Z. T. &amp; Du, Y. Z. (2015) A new species of Suwallia (Plecoptera: Chloroperlidae) from China. Zootaxa, 4018 (2), 297 - 300." type="journal article" year="2015">Chen &amp; Du 2015</bibRefCitation>
), and pale tibiae. The aedeagus of 
<taxonomicName id="9CC44D4D2438FF46FCB59C2CFC113016" authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="2019" box="[838,936,857,883]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Suwallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jihuae">
<emphasis id="69B0EADC2438FF46FCB59C2CFC113016" box="[838,936,857,883]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">S. jihuae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not everted since only the 
<typeStatus id="847F886C2438FF46FAFB9C2CFAD33016" box="[1288,1386,857,883]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">holotype</typeStatus>
was available for study and eversion of the aedeagus is often problematic. However, the visible external characters, such as the color pattern combined with the sclerite of tergum 10 can easily distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="9CC44D4D2438FF46FBC29CD5FB2A30DC" authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="2019" box="[1073,1171,927,954]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Suwallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jihuae">
<emphasis id="69B0EADC2438FF46FBC29CD5FB2A30DC" box="[1073,1171,927,954]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">S. jihuae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from congeners known from 
<collectingCountry id="23D3765E2438FF46FF269CB1FEF830B8" box="[213,321,963,990]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">East Asia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
